TITLE: Creating and Initializing an OPC UA Server using node-opcua in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to import the node-opcua SDK modules and instantiate an OPCUAServer object with specific options such as port and resource path. It also includes server build information setup and demonstrates asynchronous initialization of the server, preparing it for further configuration. Dependencies include the node-opcua package and Node.js runtime. The snippet establishes a foundation for creating and running an OPC UA server.
SOURCE: https://github.com/node-opcua/node-opcua/blob/master/documentation/creating_a_server.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const { OPCUAServer, Variant, DataType, StatusCodes} = require("node-opcua");

// Let's create an instance of OPCUAServer
const server = new OPCUAServer({
    port: 4334, // the port of the listening socket of the server
    resourcePath: "/UA/MyLittleServer", // this path will be added to the endpoint resource name
    buildInfo : {
        productName: "MySampleServer1",
        buildNumber: "7658",
        buildDate: new Date(2014,5,2)
    }
});

(async ()=>{
    await server.initialize();
    console.log("initialized");
    // post initialization steps here
    // start the server can be called later
})();
```

