TITLE: Starting the OPC UA Server and Retrieving Endpoint URL in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet explains how to start the OPC UA server asynchronously, enabling it to listen for client connections, and how to obtain and log the primary server endpoint URL. The start method accepts a callback triggered on server start completion. The endpoint URL is retrieved from the server's endpoints array and endpointDescriptions method, providing clients with the necessary connection information. This requires a fully initialized server instance.
SOURCE: https://github.com/node-opcua/node-opcua/blob/master/documentation/creating_a_server.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
server.start(function() {
    console.log("Server is now listening ... ( press CTRL+C to stop)");
    console.log("port ", server.endpoints[0].port);
    // display endpoint url
    const endpointUrl = server.endpoints[0].endpointDescriptions()[0].endpointUrl;
    console.log(" the primary server endpoint url is ", endpointUrl );
});
```

