TITLE: Writing Data to File with ClientFile - Javascript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates writing data to the OPC UA file node using the 'write()' method. Data must be provided as a Node.js Buffer, and writing occurs at the current position. This method requires the file to be opened in a writable mode.
SOURCE: https://github.com/node-opcua/node-opcua/blob/master/packages/node-opcua-file-transfer/readme.md#_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const dataToWrite = Buffer.from("Some data");

const mode = OpenFileMode.ReadWriteAppend;
await clientFile.open(mode);
await clientFile.write(dataToWrite);
```

