TITLE: Reading Data from File with ClientFile - Javascript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to read a specified number of bytes from the OPC UA file node using the 'read()' method. Reading starts from the current position. This method requires the file to be opened in a readable mode and returns a Buffer.
SOURCE: https://github.com/node-opcua/node-opcua/blob/master/packages/node-opcua-file-transfer/readme.md#_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const mode = OpenFileMode.ReadWriteAppend;
await clientFile.open(mode);

// read 200 bytes from position 32
await clientFile.setPosition([0,32]);
const data: Buffer = await clientFile.read(200);
```

