DESCRIPTION: Reads the OpenWeatherMap API key from a local file using Node.js's fs module. The snippet assumes the API key is stored as plain text in 'openweathermap.key' in the project root. Returns contents as a Buffer by default; convert to string if necessary. Requires the 'fs' module.
SOURCE: https://github.com/node-opcua/node-opcua/blob/master/documentation/create_a_weather_station.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const fs = require("fs");
const key = fs.readFileSync("openweathermap.key");
```

